    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-18T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-18T03:00:00-05:00" n="787"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94112/281: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-18T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 18, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 19—1:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1115. Japanese Consulate General informed this office orally this afternoon that
                    the Japanese Navy and Military will permit the navigation <pb facs="0799"
                        n="795" xml:id="pg_795"/> of the Yangtze by third power commercial shipping
                    as far up as Nanking in the near future under regulations to be announced
                    later.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping, Chungking, Tokyo and Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
